.TH "svc_addsock" 9 "svc_addsock" "May 2021" "Kernel Hacker's Manual" LINUX
.SH NAME
svc_addsock \- add a listener socket to an RPC service
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B "int" svc_addsock
.BI "(struct svc_serv *serv "  ","
.BI "const int fd "  ","
.BI "char *name_return "  ","
.BI "const size_t len "  ","
.BI "const struct cred *cred "  ");"
.SH ARGUMENTS
.IP "serv" 12
pointer to RPC service to which to add a new listener
.IP "fd" 12
file descriptor of the new listener
.IP "name_return" 12
pointer to buffer to fill in with name of listener
.IP "len" 12
size of the buffer
.IP "cred" 12
credential
.SH "DESCRIPTION"
Fills in socket name and returns positive length of name if successful.
Name is terminated with '\n'.  On error, returns a negative errno
value.
